## Design Overview

The solution uses a **link-state** approach: each node shares its full known
topology with direct neighbours over UDP, so every node can eventually
learn the entire graph and run Dijkstra locally.

### Design Patterns

| Pattern   | Location              | Purpose                                      |
|-----------|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Command   | commands/base.py      | Each command is an object with execute(node)  |
| Strategy  | core/dijkstra.py      | Routing algorithm is swappable                |
| Factory   | commands/factory.py   | Parses STDIN into typed Command objects       |
| Facade    | core/node.py          | Node is the single entry point for all state  |

### Threading Model

Four threads run concurrently (no hardcoded sleep/buffer times):

| Thread              | Role                                       | Sync Mechanism            |
|---------------------|--------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Main (STDIN)        | Reads commands and UPDATE packets          | Direct calls              |
| Socket listener     | Receives topology from neighbours via UDP  | lock + routing_event.set  |
| Sender              | Broadcasts UPDATE every UpdateInterval     | lock + has_changes flag   |
| Routing calculator  | Computes Dijkstra when signalled           | routing_event.wait()      |

### Synchronisation Primitives

| Primitive       | Type    | Purpose                                          |
|-----------------|---------|--------------------------------------------------|
| lock            | RLock   | Protects all shared mutable state                |
| routing_event   | Event   | Signals routing thread (no polling)              |
| _print_lock     | Lock    | Prevents interleaved multi-line STDOUT output    |

Lock ordering: lock -> _print_lock (never reversed, prevents deadlock).

## Supported Commands

All commands from the spec are implemented:

| Command              | Description                                      |
|----------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| CHANGE               | Update the cost of an edge to a neighbour        |
| FAIL                 | Mark a node as down (stop broadcasts if self)    |
| RECOVER              | Bring a node back up                             |
| QUERY                | Print least-cost path from this node             |
| QUERY PATH           | Print least-cost path between any two nodes      |
| RESET                | Restore original config and re-broadcast         |
| BATCH UPDATE         | Process a file of commands sequentially           |
| MERGE (bonus)        | Absorb one node into another                     |
| SPLIT (bonus)        | Partition the graph alphabetically               |
| CYCLE DETECT (bonus) | Report whether the graph contains a cycle        |
